      • onActionSave

        public void onActionSave​(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
                  throws java.io.IOException
        This method saves the data input into the form and adds it as an InHouse or Outsourced part. The form alternates between creating a InHouse or Outsourced part depending on which radio button is selected. It also validates proper data is being input.

        RUNTIME ERROR: I experienced a java.lang.NumberFormatException when attempting to generate the machine ID in the fields. I had to make separate sections for passed in InHouse and Outsourced parts because Strings cannot be set as an int.

        Parameters:
        actionEvent - The actions of clicking the save button
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
